The LVM2 package is a package that manages logical partitions.
It allows spanning of file systems across multiple physical disks
and disk partitions and provides for dynamic growing or shrinking
of logical partitions. 
LVM2 refers to the userspace toolset that provide logical
volume management facilities on linux.
It is reasonably backwards-compatible with the original LVM toolset. 

